cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "mech_gov: Mechanical Governance for LLM Decisions"
abstract: >-
  A model-agnostic Python framework for enforcing and measuring governance on
  LLM decisions in high-stakes settings, contrasting a text-only governance
  regime (R1) with mechanical enforcement (R2) and an adaptive regime (R3),
  with governance metrics and a synthetic decision dataset.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Santander AI Lab"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-12"
license: Apache-2.0
repository-code: "https://github.com/SantanderAI/mech-gov-framework"
url: "https://github.com/SantanderAI/mech-gov-framework"
keywords:
  - llm
  - ai-governance
  - ai-safety
  - learning-to-defer
  - decision-systems
  - evaluation
